      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The MACRS (Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System) formula for a 5-year property asset is a bit more complex, but I can guide you through it. The formula is:\n\nMACRS = (Cost - Residual Value) / (Year 1 + Year 2 + Year 3 + Year 4 + Year 5)\n\nWhere:\n- Cost is the initial cost of the asset\n- Residual Value is the asset's estimated value at the end of the asset's useful life (in this case, 5 years)\n- Year 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5 are the years the asset is depreciated\n\nFor example, if the asset cost $100,000 and has a residual value of $20,000, the MACRS calculation would be:\n\nMACRS = ($100,000 - $20,000) / (100,000 + 50,000 + 33,333 + 25,000 + 20,000)\nMACRS = $80,000 / $228,333\nMACRS = 0.3495 (or approximately 35.49%)\n\nThis means the asset is depreciated by 35.49% in the first year,",
      "source": "target",
